松露有一股類似[[煤氣|煤氣]]的[[雄烯酮|雄烯酮]]的味道，自古便有許多人為之著迷。
{{cquote|那股香气曾被形容为“人间所无，有点难以置信，殆凡气味绝佳者概如是也。”那气味渗透力之强也十分惊人，可以力透层层纸张，甚至塑胶袋。只需要轻嗅一下就够了，若是吸得浓一点就过头了，会叫你食欲全无的，因为那气味好浓又好像臭豆腐。|《有关品味》<ref name="有关品味">{{cite book | author=彼得·梅尔 | authorlink =彼得·梅尔 | title = 有关品味}}</ref>}}
1825年時[[法國|法國]]著名美食家[[布里亞-薩瓦蘭|布里亞-薩瓦蘭]]（Jean Anthelme Brillat-Savarin）在其著作《[[味覺生理學|味覺生理學]]》（''{{lang|fr|Physiologie du Goût}}''）中便盛讚松露為「廚房的[[鑽石|鑽石]]」。[[歐洲|歐洲]]人將松露與[[魚子醬|魚子醬]]、[[鵝肝|鵝肝]]並列「世界三大珍饈」，屬於高貴食材之一，特別是[[法國|法國]]產的[[黑松露|黑松露]]（''Tuber melanosporum'' Vitt.）與[[意大利|意大利]]產的[[白松露|白松露]]（''Tuber magnatum'' Pico）評價最高。

==生物学==
[[File:Truffle_Evolution.jpg|thumb]]
松露的[[菌丝体|菌丝体]]形成几个树种的根[[共生|共生]]的[[菌根|菌根]]关系，包括[[榉木|榉木]]、[[杨木|杨木]]、柞、[[桦|桦]]、[[鹅耳枥|鹅耳枥]]、[[榛子|榛子]]和[[松树|松树]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.truffle-uk.co.uk/home_uk_summer_truffle.php |title=‘finds’ registered at Royal Botannical Gardens, Kew |accessdate=2008-05-17 |publisher=Truffle UK Ltd. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080918080349/http://www.truffle-uk.co.uk/home_uk_summer_truffle.php |archive-date=2008-09-18 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.angelfire.com/wizard/kimbrough/Textbook/NonCultivatedEdibleFungi_blue.htm |title=Non-cultivated Edible Fleshy Fungi |accessdate=2008-05-17 |quote=...it has been known for more than a century that truffles were mycorrhizal on various trees such as oak, beech, birch, hazels, and a few others |archive-date=2021-03-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210315143933/https://www.angelfire.com/wizard/kimbrough/Textbook/NonCultivatedEdibleFungi_blue.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。它们更喜欢排水良好和中性或[[碱|碱]]性的泥质或钙质土壤<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.huh.harvard.edu/collections/fof/newsletters/newslspring2006.pdf |title=Basidiomycota truffles: Cup fungi go underground |accessdate=2008-05-17 |author=Karen Hansen |editor=K. Griffith |date=Spring 2006 |work=Newsletter of the FRIENDS of the FARLOW |publisher=Harvard University |format=PDF |quote=Generally, truffles seems to prefer. warm, fairly dry climates and calcareous soils |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081121001628/http://www.huh.harvard.edu/collections/fof/newsletters/newslSpring2006.pdf |archivedate=2008-11-21 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bugs.bio.usyd.edu.au/Mycology/UsesOf_Fungi/primaryProduction/mushroomProd.shtml |title=Mushroom Production |accessdate=2008-05-17 |author= |date=June 2004 |work=Mycology - Uses of Fungi |publisher=University of Sydney |quote=The soil of the truffiere tends to be alkaline, calcareous, and well drained. |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080501070447/http://bugs.bio.usyd.edu.au/Mycology/UsesOf_Fungi/primaryProduction/mushroomProd.shtml |archivedate=2008-05-01 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。松露根据种类的不同，可以发现埋在枯枝落叶和土壤之间。

==松露种植==
